---
The Bell Synod was the ritual clergy body of the Gloamvault, one of three interlocked offices
governing Kel'Shadra's oath-archive institution alongside the Ash Scriptorium and Reliquary
Host. Synod priests controlled confession intake, managed processional liturgies, and determined
whose words were deemed admissible memory within the institution's witness framework. In doctrine
they balanced against the Scriptorium and Host; in practice they withheld absolution to force
favorable record outcomes, making them the primary gatekeeper of legal identity. The Synod's
bells served as administrative communication infrastructure: specific sequences summoned
assemblies, authorized transfers, and signaled archive classifications. Bell silence was a
doctrinal event with immediate operational consequences across all Kel'Shadra offices. During
the Night of Unsounded Bells, Synod hardliners ordered silence to suppress a reform bloc's
attempt to expose falsified absolution records, triggering cascade failure. The Synod claimed
to witness truth and offer absolution; internally it enforced which truths entered the record
at all. The Ash Scriptorium converted testimony into binding law, but the Synod chose what
testimony crossed the intake threshold first.

flags MIDGAARD
