Deltari Reed Law requires witnessed measurement: a fact carries evidentiary weight only when
two independent observers confirm it using the same calibration standard. Bell Synod intake
records fail this standard systematically. Deltari archivists working on Rakuen's Garden Ledger
reconstruction identified Synod records as uncorroborated throughout: no external confirmation
of what was submitted, no independent record of classification decisions, no counter-signature
